document.full_text: left-wing nationalist ollanta humala won the first round of peru's presidential election on sunday and looked set to face rightist keiko fujimori in what could be a bruising run-off in june, an unofficial quick count of ballots showed.
document.title: humala wins peru 1st round, eyes fujimori in run-off
lines_and_colors: left-wing nationalist ollanta humala won the first round of peru's presidential election on sunday and looked set to face rightist keiko fujimori in what could be a bruising run-off in june, an unofficial quick count of ballots showed.
